<br>
He chuckled as he waited for a reaction.  It wasn't as if many of them hadn't come to him in the past in search of a father for their children.  After all Hera couldn't always assist in this endeavor and he was all the more willing to help.  It was, after all, his pleasure.  <br>
<br>
With the temple now on the boundary of Themiscrya, he had made himself even more accessible to these warrior women. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamazonqueenyakut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amazon Queen Yakut </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/01 6:27:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Temple in Themiscrya</span><hr size=1> Yakut was traveling through Themiscrya and she saw the new temple and thought to herself:<br>
'Gods...cant live with them cant live with out them' <br>
<br>
Yakut was not a follower of the gods though; she followed her Amazon Ancients but she was not one to disrespect the gods. She knew they could wipe out her little mortal ass in a heart beat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen of the Gods</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#993300>(6/10/01 3:57:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Another temple...and of Zeus?!</span><hr size=1> In the middle of the temple, a burst of light appeared in among the few priests and priestess's who had begun to assemble.  In the light, appeared Hera.  Her eyes were narrowed as she scanned the room and then set upon a statue of Zeus in the middle. &quot;How dare he!&quot; she hissed at the statue.  &quot;In the land of the amazons no less!&quot;  It was bad enough that he had cheated on her with some amazons, but to build a temple for that purpose.  He had lost it.  Never the less...this was not his territory.<br>
Her pale icy blue eyes turned to those of peacock feather eyelets as she slowely turned her wicked gaze to almost melt those who met her glance.  &quot;I would suggest you leave....and leave at once,&quot;she growled. <br>
With that, the few priests and priestess's quickly grabbed what they could and ran out of the temple.<br>
Hera raised both delicate hands out to her side, her palms facing outwards. &quot;This is too, far dear husband,&quot;she snarled. And suddenly light surrounded her slim body and shot out to all sides away from her disintegrating the new temple to nothing but the tiniest dusts.  It's white marble nothing but shimmering dust on that which if fell upon or danced away on the breeze.  <br>
Leaving Hera standing there in her black dress, and her eyes back to pale icy blue.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#993300>(6/11/01 10:17:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/artemis3.bmp></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Temple in Themiscrya</span><hr size=1> ~in a burst of green light Artemis appeared standing besides Hera, dressed in her hunting outfit of a black leather halter and black leather skirt, tight boots to her knees, over that she wore a breastplate forged by Hephestis, she turned to Hera sighing~<br>
