&quot;My fellow Olympians,&quot; she said as dignified as she could. &quot;I believe I have business to tend to.&quot; In a flash of light, the Queen of the Gods...dissappeared. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#993300>(6/20/01 12:28:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=224.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Amused</span><hr size=1> ::On the outskirts of Themiscrya Poseidon gazes on the events that have just arose. His brother made a temple there, which has not lasted so long. He begins to speak to himself. Out of the view of the others.::<br>
<br>
